	dprr:hasNoteText "ref. 335" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8766> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8766" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 752, footnote 387" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7943> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7943" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cos. 68. Praetor urbanus or peregrinus 71 (B. W. Frier, TAPhA 113, 1983, 224-225, 229; cf. MRR 2.122).\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7750> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7750" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Monetalis. In MRR 2.433, and Index 538, refer also to Crawford, RRC 1.333- 336, no. 335, 96 B.C.? With C. Mall. and A. Alb. Too early a date for the consul of 68 B.C.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4641> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4641" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "CIL 12.2.905, 956; Dio 36.4.1; Chr. 354 (Metello et Vatia); Fast. Hyd. (Marcio Rege et Metello), so also Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; and on Marcius, CIL 12.2.747, and perhaps 660 (but see 118, Consuls). See Degrassi 131, 488f. Metellus died early in the year (Dio 36.4.1). Cilicia was withdrawn from the command of Lucullus and assigned to Marcius (Dio 36.2.2; cf. Suet. Iul. 8; see 67, Promagistrates)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4640> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4640" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "1 A brother of Metellus Creticus, and son of C. Metellus Caprarius and grandson of Q. Metellus Macedonicus (Cic. Verr. 1.27; CIL 12.2.746)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4580> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4580" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Propraetor in Sicily, and successor to Verres (Cic. Verr. 1.27; 2.3.152; Liv. Per. 98; Oros. 6.3.5, all with the title Praetor). He improved the administration of the province, even while placing obstacles in the way of the prosecution of Verres (Cic. Verr. 1.27; 2.2.10 and 62ff., and 138-139 and 160-164 and 187; 2.3.43ff., and 121ff., and 144 and 152ff.; 2.4.141 and 147; 2.5.55 and 129; Ps.-Ascon. 185, 213f., 260 Stangl). He defended the island against pirates (Liv. Per. 98; Oros. 6.3.5)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4534> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4534" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Probably, but not certainly, the Metellus, Praetor, mentioned in Cic. Tull. 39. See 70, Promagistrates." .
